  "notes": [
    "All transfer applicants must satisfy University of California admissions eligibility requirements as well as meeting campus admission selection criteria. Completing the UC transfer admission requirements in English and mathematics by the end of the fall term prior to the fall application quarter makes an applicant more competitive for admission to UCSB. All admission requirements must be completed by the end of spring prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility requirements and admission to UCSB, please visit the Admissions website: www.admissions.ucsb.edu This articulation agreement lists course-to-course or sequence-to-sequence substitutions for preparation in the major. Transfer students are strongly encouraged to complete as many major preparatory courses as possible prior to enrolling at UCSB. Completion of all major preparatory courses is not an admissions requirement, but some majors require certain courses to be completed prior to transfer with a specified GPA. Completion or near completion of major preparatory courses will help students move more efficiently toward graduation after transfer. Please note that the course \"equivalencies\" do not necessarily apply to UCSB general education. For information concerning satisfaction of UCSB general education requirements, please refer to the General Education/Breadth articulation agreement. Advanced Placement (AP) and International Baccalaureate (IB) exams may or may not be used to meet course requirements, depending on the exam. Please refer to the AP Chart and IB Chart in the UCSB General Catalog for information on how we use AP and IB exams.",
    "Please visit the department's website to learn more about this major: www.medievalstudies.ucsb.edu PREPARATION FOR THE MAJOR: Two courses from the following: History 2A, 2B, 4A, 4B (Transfer applicants do not need to complete all Preparation for the Major in order to be admitted, but should complete as much as possible before transferring so they will be prepared to progress in the major at UCSB.) Note: A reading knowledge of Latin and a modern European language will be necessary for those pursuing graduate programs. However, it is not required for the major.",
    "Breadth Requirements: Most of the Discipline Distribution Breadth Requirement and Area Distribution Breadth Requirement will be fulfilled after transfer with upper-division courses, but one lower-division transfer course can apply to one of these requirements . Articulated community college courses are all lower-division, so only the lower-division options are listed here. There are many upper-division options at UCSB. A. Discipline Distribution Breadth Requirement (five courses from at least three different areas, but most or all of that will be completed after transfer) A-1) History : History 2B, 4A, 4B, 46A, 49A A-2) Art, Architecture or Music (image, sound, material objects) : History of Art and Architecture 6M A-3) Literature or Written Culture (text, writing) : Comparative Literature 30A, 50A; Chinese 80; French 50AX A-4) Religion, Philosophy or Science : Chinese 48; Philosophy 20B; Religious Studies 4, 23, 26, 27, 33, 47, 48, 73, 80B B. Area Distribution Breadth Requirement (four courses from at least 2 different areas/diaspora, but most or all of that will be completed after transfer) B-1) Africa : History 2B, 49A B-2) Byzantium/Eastern Christendom : no lower-division options B-3) East Asia : Religious Studies 4, 23, 47, 48, 73 B-4) Europe : Comparative Literature 30A, 50A; French 50AX; History 2B, 4B; History of Art and Architecture 6M B-5) Islamicate World: History 2B, 46A; Philosophy 20B B-6) Jewish Studies: Religious Studies 26, 27 B-7) Mediterranean : History 2B, 4A, 15 B-8) Latin America : no lower-division options"
  ]
